event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_02b3f8edec7d19850169fb383634b881978e3cbe4e69459c70","output_index":0,"sequence_number":107,"summary_index":0,"text":"**Calculating distance from Paris**\n\nI'm figuring out the distance from Paris based on train travel. The first train covers a distance of 80 km from 3 PM to 4 PM, plus an additional distance of 173.333 km during the following 2 hours and 10 minutes. That totals 253.333 km. Alternatively, I can compute it directly: from 3 PM to 6:10 PM is 3.166 hours, multiplying that by 80 gives the same result. I can express this as 253 km and 333 meters or just round to 253.33 km."}

