event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_02b3f8edec7d19850169fb383634b881978e3cbe4e69459c70","output_index":0,"sequence_number":213,"summary_index":1,"text":"**Calculating distance from Paris using the second train**\n\nI can also compute the distance from Paris using the second train traveling from Lyon. It travels 216.67 km when I multiply 100 km/h by 2.16667 hours. If I check the total distance, it sums to 470 km. The meeting time is 6:10 PM, at which point the distance from Paris is 253 1/3 km. I can break it down: the first train travels 80 km in an hour, leaving 390 km at 4 PM, with the relative speed being 180 km/h."}

