event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_02b3f8edec7d19850169fb383634b881978e3cbe4e69459c70","output_index":0,"sequence_number":345,"summary_index":2,"text":"**Calculating total distance from Paris**\n\nI can also compute the distance after 4 PM. It travels 80 km for 13/6 hours, which equals 173 1/3 km. Adding the initial 80 km gives a total of 253 1/3 km. To keep it concise, I'll summarize the steps: \n\n1. Lead distance: 80 km.\n2. Remaining distance: 390 km.\n3. Time to meet: 390/(80 + 100) = 13/6 hours or 2 hours and 10 minutes, so meeting at 6:10 PM.\n4. Therefore, the total distance from Paris is calculated as 80 * (1 + 13/6) = 253 1/3 km."}

event: response.reasoning_summary_part.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_part.done","item_id":"rs_02b3f8edec7d19850169fb383634b881978e3cbe4e69459c70","output_index":0,"part":{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Calculating total distance from Paris**\n\nI can also compute the distance after 4 PM. It travels 80 km for 13/6 hours, which equals 173 1/3 km. Adding the initial 80 km gives a total of 253 1/3 km. To keep it concise, I'll summarize the steps: \n\n1. Lead distance: 80 km.\n2. Remaining distance: 390 km.\n3. Time to meet: 390/(80 + 100) = 13/6 hours or 2 hours and 10 minutes, so meeting at 6:10 PM.\n4. Therefore, the total distance from Paris is calculated as 80 * (1 + 13/6) = 253 1/3 km."},"sequence_number":346,"summary_index":2}

event: response.output_item.done
data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"id":"rs_02b3f8edec7d19850169fb383634b881978e3cbe4e69459c70","type":"reasoning","summary":[{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Calculating distance from Paris**\n\nI'm figuring out the distance from Paris based on train travel. The first train covers a distance of 80 km from 3 PM to 4 PM, plus an additional distance of 173.333 km during the following 2 hours and 10 minutes. That totals 253.333 km. Alternatively, I can compute it directly: from 3 PM to 6:10 PM is 3.166 hours, multiplying that by 80 gives the same result. I can express this as 253 km and 333 meters or just round to 253.33 km."},{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Calculating distance from Paris using the second train**\n\nI can also compute the distance from Paris using the second train traveling from Lyon. It travels 216.67 km when I multiply 100 km/h by 2.16667 hours. If I check the total distance, it sums to 470 km. The meeting time is 6:10 PM, at which point the distance from Paris is 253 1/3 km. I can break it down: the first train travels 80 km in an hour, leaving 390 km at 4 PM, with the relative speed being 180 km/h."},{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Calculating total distance from Paris**\n\nI can also compute the distance after 4 PM. It travels 80 km for 13/6 hours, which equals 173 1/3 km. Adding the initial 80 km gives a total of 253 1/3 km. To keep it concise, I'll summarize the steps: \n\n1. Lead distance: 80 km.\n2. Remaining distance: 390 km.\n3. Time to meet: 390/(80 + 100) = 13/6 hours or 2 hours and 10 minutes, so meeting at 6:10 PM.\n4. Therefore, the total distance from Paris is calculated as 80 * (1 + 13/6) = 253 1/3 km."}]},"output_index":0,"sequence_number":347}

