data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_02b3f8edec7d19850169fb38467e888197827c7a2304f1e8c2","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":459,"text":"From 3–4 pm the Paris train goes 80 km, so at 4 pm the remaining distance is 470 − 80 = 390 km.  \nTheir closing speed is 80 + 100 = 180 km/h, so time to meet after 4 pm = 390/180 = 13/6 h = 2 h 10 min.\n\nThey meet at 4:00 + 2:10 = 6:10 pm.\n\nDistance from Paris = distance traveled by the Paris train = 80 ×"}

